**Abstract:**
Working notes titled "Assent" examining the difference between narratives and statements, consent versus assent. Argues that the medieval theologians mistakenly read the Bible as a series of statements to be assented to rather than as narratives to be heard. Draws on Elias's defense of Plato's myths and MacIntyre's observations on Robertson Smith. Develops a theory of linguistic communication based on oral rather than written language.

